                In <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>onorem</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omus</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ivinae</ex></expan></supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/>horo<supplied reason="lost">logium pecunia s</supplied>ua <lb n="3"/>et aed<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">em cum ornamentis? suis</supplied> <lb n="4"/>omn<supplied reason="lost">ibus et signis<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="5"/>Iucun<supplied reason="lost">d</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="6"/>Iuc<supplied reason="lost">und</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Zwei nicht aneinanderpassende Fragmente erhalten. Fundjahr und Maße beziehen sich auf das linke Fragment (a); rechtes Fragment (b): Fundjahr: 1946; Maße: (67) (33) x 22 cm. Z. 4-7: Nach Wiegels handelt es sich bei den Dedikanten vermutlich um dieselben Personen wie in der Grabinschrift HD056817.</p>
            </div>
